supportDesc.foliation: : Modern (early modern?) foliation in ink. quoque similiter execramur

collation.catchwords: Catchwords present, but lost on some quires due to trimming.

p.note: Top left corner: National Library book label with current signum.
Upper part of page, in brown ink by a 19th century hand: Sancti Hieronymi Epistolae xlii.

binding.p: Early modern binding. Light brown leather over wooden boards. 4 double raised bands and endbands. , stamped in gold: A 224.
binding.decoNote: Simple blind tooled decoration consisting of panels and x-shapes.
binding.condition: According to a librarian's note from the 19th century the binding has been repaired. The front cover had been detached and the spine was very worn. Before the repair the spine had a sticker attached to it, on which no 18 was written.

history.origin: Italy? , 15th-16th century. Origin and dating conjecture based on the script.
history.provenance: Exact origin and early provenance unknown. The manuscript has been at the National LIbrarysince the 17th century. The two signa on refers to Jaches's catalgoue of 1698 (U 122), where it is listed as 214; and the catalogue of 1734 (U 125e), where it is listed as Theol. in 4o nr 8.

msItem.title: Collection of letters and other texts

note.p: : ruled for two columns, but no text.

supportDesc.condition: Textblock dirty at the beginning and end, which may indicate that it have been stored without binding for some time.

layout.note: Blind ruling. Last quire does not contain any text but is ruled in ink for two columns.

p.note:
Top left corner, in black ink by modern hand: No 8 in 4o
; top margin, in brown ink by a modern hand: S. Hieronymi Epistolae; below the main text, in brown ink, perhaps by the scribe: οις αλυχω λιαν ευλυχω ; bottom right corner, in brown ink by an early modern hand: 214. Nov. Num..
Occasional corrections by the scribe or a contemporary hand in the margins. Letters numbered (2-42) in brown ink next to the rubric, date of hand unknown.

decoDesc.p: Main text in brown ink, rubrics in red.
decoDesc.decoNote: Space reserved for an opening initial over 9 lines and 2-4 lines at the beginning of each letter. Guide letters written in the margins.
